    "narrative": "The clear standout for the Austin Waves today is **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 score cements him as the anchor of the lineup. Facing Houser, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and a highly favorable 14% platoon edge, positioning him to lead the offensive charge. Following him closely is **Marcell Ozuna** (64.98), who capitalizes on a 10% wind-out advantage at his venue, and **Miguel Vargas** (64.07), who finds himself in an ideal scenario with a leadoff spot and favorable weather conditions. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.80) faces a decent matchup against Bradley, his score remains strong despite a slight negative adjustment for platoon dynamics, proving his reliability in the 3-hole.\n\nThe roster configuration reflects our aggressive prioritization of efficiency against top-tier arms. We have opted to start **Kyle Tucker** (57.87) despite a daunting matchup against deGrom; his elite base projection remains too high to bench, even with a 16% penalty for the opposing ace. The tightest bench decision today involved **Josh Jung**, who scored a 55.14 against Sasaki. While **Josh Jung** carries a high 19% SP skill advantage, he was ultimately displaced by the higher combined ceiling of our middle-of-the-order starters. We are monitoring a 39% rain risk for **Jackson Merrill** (58.20); while his matchup against Freeland is favorable, the weather introduces enough volatility that we are keeping a close eye on the pre-game reports. Finally, note the caution regarding **Andy Pages** (47.63), whose score is suppressed by deGrom and the opponent's ability to limit stolen bases\u2014a critical concern given our pursuit of SB efficiency.",
